## Cushion Cut Diamond Leverback Earrings

Leverback earrings use a hinged back closure instead of a standard push-back post. More secure. Less likely to fall out. Preferred for drop and dangle styles.

**[Diamond Halo Leverback Earrings — Cushion Cut Diamonds, 18K White Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/diamond-halo-leverback-earrings-with-cushion-cut-diamonds-in-18k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315862?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
~~[$5,715](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/diamond-halo-leverback-earrings-with-cushion-cut-diamonds-in-18k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315862?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)~~ **[$2,857](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/diamond-halo-leverback-earrings-with-cushion-cut-diamonds-in-18k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315862?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — 50% off

18K white gold. Cushion center stones with diamond halo. Leverback closure. 50% off from $5,715 to $2,857.

The leverback closure is worth understanding. Push-back posts (the standard earring back) rely on tension to stay in place. They can loosen. They can fall out. Leverbacks have a hinged lever that clicks shut — physically locked. For valuable earrings, the security is real.

These work for evenings, events, and anyone who prefers wearing earrings that move and catch light rather than sitting flat against the earlobe.

The cushion shape in a leverback drop is elegant in motion. Each stone has soft, rounded corners — no sharp points catching light harshly. As the earring swings, you see the cushion's characteristic big flash pattern. It's a completely different look than a princess cut drop (sharp, angular flashes) or a round drop (consistent brilliant sparkle).

If you've ever seen someone wearing drop earrings that caught the light in an unusually warm, romantic way — cushion drops are often the explanation.

