## Expert Summary

Cushion cut diamond earrings start at [$325 for lab-grown 1/4 ct tw](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251842?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and [$623 for natural 1/4 ct tw](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251840?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab-grown dominates this category — better grade specs, lower prices, and no visible difference when worn.

Remember The Total Weight Trap. "1 ct tw" means 0.50ct per ear. Plan your purchase around how the earrings will look from the outside — per-ear carat, not total. The [1 ct tw lab studs at $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) give you half a carat per ear — the right size for most people.

The Pair Problem doesn't apply if you buy a certified pair — the stones are already matched. It only matters if you build a custom pair from individual stones. Both must be the same cushion sub-type.

For style: studs for everyday, halo studs for more presence without going dangly, leverback drops for events. Natural cushion earrings at 30% off make sense if mined origin matters to you. For everyone else, lab is the obvious choice.

