## Frequently Asked Questions

### What are cushion cut diamond earrings?
Cushion cut diamond earrings have cushion-shaped diamonds — a square or rectangular stone with rounded corners and soft edges. The cushion cut is known for its soft sparkle and pillow-like appearance. It works in studs, halo settings, drops, and leverback styles.

### How much do cushion cut diamond earrings cost?
Lab-grown cushion studs start at [$325 for 1/4 ct tw](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251842?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and go to [$5,230 for 6 ct tw](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-6-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-280410?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural cushion studs start at [$623 for 1/4 ct tw](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251840?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (currently 30% off). Price scales with carat weight, metal, and stone type.

### What does ct tw mean for diamond earrings?
"ct tw" stands for carat total weight — the combined weight of both earrings together. A 1 ct tw pair has two stones that add up to 1 carat. Each ear gets 0.50ct. This is standard practice for all earring jewelry. When you compare earring prices to individual loose stones, remember to halve the carat weight.

### What is the most popular size for cushion diamond earrings?
1 ct tw (0.50ct per ear) is the most popular size. It's visible and present on the ear without being oversized. The [lab-grown 1 ct tw at $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best-selling cushion stud at this size.

### Should I buy lab or natural cushion diamond earrings?
Lab for almost everyone. The lab studs have better grade specs (F-G/VS2-SI1 vs H-I/SI1-SI2 for natural) at a fraction of the price. The [lab 1 ct tw is $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs the [natural 1 ct tw at $3,003](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251849?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). You get better color and clarity for $1,623 less. Earrings don't get appraised or resold the way rings do. Buy lab.

### What is the Pair Problem with cushion diamond earrings?
Cushion diamonds come in two sub-types — cushion modified brilliant (crushed-ice sparkle) and cushion brilliant (larger, bolder flashes). In a pair of earrings, both stones must be the same sub-type. Mixing them creates visible asymmetry. Pre-set certified pairs handle this for you. If you build a custom pair from two individual stones, confirm both are the same sub-type and within one GIA color grade of each other.

### What is a cushion cut diamond halo earring?
A halo earring has a ring of small diamonds surrounding the center cushion stone. This makes the center look bigger and adds more sparkle without increasing center stone carat. The [cushion halo stud at $555](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-diamond-halo-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-201193?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (currently 50% off) is a strong value option for anyone who wants more visual presence than a plain solitaire stud.

### What is a cushion cut diamond leverback earring?
A leverback is a type of earring closure — a hinged lever that locks shut, more secure than a standard push-back post. The [cushion halo leverback at $2,857](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/diamond-halo-leverback-earrings-with-cushion-cut-diamonds-in-18k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315862?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (50% off) is the main cushion leverback option. Good for drop-style earrings that you don't want falling out.

### Are cushion cut diamond earrings good for everyday wear?
Yes. Stud-style cushion earrings are low-profile and secure. The rounded corners of the cushion shape don't snag on hair or clothing the way princess cut sharp corners can. Lab cushion studs in [1 ct tw at $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) or smaller are practical for daily wear.

### What is the difference between cushion cut diamond drop earrings and stud earrings?
Studs sit against the earlobe and don't move. Drops hang below the earlobe and move when you do. Studs are better for everyday. Drops are better for events and evenings when you want earrings with presence and motion. The [bezel-set cushion drop at $29,493](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-bezel-set-diamond-drop-earrings-in-18k-white-gold-6-ct-tw-item-194898?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the statement option; the leverback halo at [$2,857](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/diamond-halo-leverback-earrings-with-cushion-cut-diamonds-in-18k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315862?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the accessible version.

### What metal is best for cushion diamond earrings?
White gold for a clean, modern look. Yellow gold for warmth. Platinum for the most durable and hypoallergenic option. White gold is the most popular for cushion earrings — it lets the stone's color show its best without adding warmth. Natural cushion earrings also come in platinum for a small price premium.

### How do I choose between 1 ct tw and 2 ct tw cushion earrings?
1 ct tw = 0.50ct per ear. Good for everyday. Noticeable but not bold. 2 ct tw = 1ct per ear. Bold. You see them across a room. If you want earrings for all occasions, 1 ct tw. If you want earrings that make a statement, 2 ct tw. The [lab 2 ct tw at $2,110](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251857?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best value option at that size.

### What color grade should cushion diamond earrings have?
F-G for lab earrings (what all the lab stud options use). H-I for natural earrings (standard for set jewelry at earring size). At earring size — where stones are small and viewed from a distance — H-I reads as white in practice. You're not looking at the stone under magnification. You're seeing it in motion on someone's ear. H-I works. F-G is just better because lab makes it affordable.

### Are cushion cut diamond stud earrings a good gift?
Yes. Cushion studs are versatile. They work for everyday and special occasions. The shape is softer than princess or round — it suits people who like the cushion's aesthetic. The [lab 1 ct tw at $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is a strong gift at that budget. The [halo stud at $555](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/cushion-cut-diamond-halo-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-201193?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best-value gift option.

### Do cushion cut diamond earrings look smaller than round at the same carat?
Yes, slightly. Cushion cuts are cut deeper than round brilliants. More weight hides in the depth, less spreads across the face. A 0.50ct cushion and a 0.50ct round won't look identical on the ear — the round spreads a little wider. It's not a dramatic difference, but it's real. If maximum face-up size matters to you, buy one step up in ct tw when choosing cushion over round.

### What setting style works best for cushion cut diamond stud earrings?
Four-prong corner settings work best for cushion studs. The prongs sit at the corners and anchor the stone cleanly. Simple solitaires with a very round bezel can make a square cushion look like an irregular circle — the contrast between the round prongs and the cushion's shape highlights the irregularity. Corner-set prongs match the cushion's square geometry. Halo settings also work extremely well — the round halo around the cushion center creates an intentional contrast that looks elegant, not awkward.
